cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper deals with depth sensing and 3D reconstruction, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of machine learning techniques for depth inference suggests that the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The hourglass network architecture used in the paper is a popular deep learning model for image processing tasks, which further supports the inclusion of cs.LG (machine learning) as a likely category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) as it involves rendering and producing 3D disparity maps.
